newsitem.title: USA: CBOT wheat ends lower on export woes, crop talk.
newsitem.headline: CBOT wheat ends lower on export woes, crop talk.

text.p: CBOT wheat futures closed mostly lower on persistent reminders of competition for wheat exports plus talk about overall good conditions for the emerging 1997 U.S. winter wheat crop, traders said.
Overall fundamentals were little changed and remained bearish, they said, with Algeria overnight buying 100,000 tonnes of wheat from Argentina rather than the U.S.
Traders also said key technical indicators including the moving averages showed wheat remained in a bearish mode.
Wheat closed 3-1/2 cents per bushel lower to 1-1/4 higher, with December down 3-1/2 at $3.81.
Wheat futures volume was estimated at 12,000 contracts, down from 14,491 Tuesday, according to the CBOT.
In wheat options, Cargill Investor Services bought 200 July $3.50 puts at nine cents and First Options bought 200 March $4.60 calls at one cent, traders said.
Wheat options volume was estimated at 4,000 contracts, down from 5,621 Tuesday.
